# **International Distribution Agreement**
Creates comprehensive international distribution agreements for appointing distributors across borders, addressing regulatory and transactional risks and ensuring compliance with export controls, sanctions, and product regulations.

## **Prerequisites**
1. Party details and roles
2. Products and regulatory classification
3. Territory and sales channels
4. Pricing, payment terms, and credit support
5. Incoterm selection and logistics arrangements
6. Applicable compliance requirements

## **Output Structure / Process**
1. Intake checklist completion  
2. Drafting core agreement sections  
3. Selecting and customizing clauses from clause map  
4. Ensuring compliance via checklists  
5. Reviewing for jurisdictional and regulatory consistency  
6. Finalizing template and delivery  

**Intake Checklist**

| Item                       | Options / Notes                                             | Required |
|----------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|----------|
| Party names and addresses  | Full legal names, contact info                              | Yes      |
| Product descriptions       | Including HS codes, classifications                         | Yes      |
| Territory                  | Exclusive/non-exclusive, geographic scope                   | Yes      |
| Pricing and payment terms  | Currency, credit terms, invoicing                            | Yes      |
| Incoterms                  | Use latest ICC edition, specify named place/port            | Yes      |
| Compliance screening       | Export controls, sanctions lists, anti-corruption screening | Yes      |
| Regulatory registrations   | Local product registrations or approvals                     | If applicable |

**Clause Map**

| Section               | Must Cover                                      | Options / Notes                                  |
|-----------------------|------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| Appointment           | Distributor status, exclusivity                  | Sub-distributors rights and approvals           |
| Territory             | Define scope and any restrictions                | Channels authorized for sales                    |
| Ordering & Pricing    | Order procedures, price adjustments               | Performance targets/minimum purchase obligations |
| Payment Terms         | Currency, invoicing, credit support               | Late payment penalties                            |
| Delivery & Risk       | Incoterms, transfer of title and risk             | Inspection rights                                |
| Warranty & Returns    | Product warranties, defective return procedures  | Remedies and liability limits                     |
| Compliance            | Export controls, sanctions, anti-corruption      | Screening obligations, audit rights               |
| Intellectual Property | License to use trademarks and brands              | Restrictions, quality control                      |
| Confidentiality       | Handling of confidential information               | Duration and scope                                |
| Term & Termination    | Duration, renewal, termination rights              | Post-termination obligations, sell-off period    |
| Governing Law & Dispute| Governing law clause and arbitration/mediation    | Consider New York Convention enforceability       |
| CISG Opt-Out          | Exclude CISG application if desired                | Specify in governing law clause                   |
| Liability & Indemnity | Limitation of liability, indemnities                | Carve-outs for IP, confidentiality, compliance   |
| Force Majeure         | Excusable delays and conditions                     | Notice requirements                               |
| Assignment            | Restrictions on assignment and change of control   | Consent rights                                    |
| Relationship          | Confirm independent contractor status               | No agency or partnership intent                   |
| Audit Rights          | Distributor audit for compliance verifications     | Anti-corruption and regulatory compliance         |
| Records & Reporting   | Record keeping and reporting obligations             | Inspection rights                                 |

**Compliance Checklist**

- [ ] Screen parties against export control and sanctions lists  
- [ ] Confirm compliance with anti-corruption laws (e.g., FCPA, UK Bribery Act)  
- [ ] Verify product regulatory registrations and classifications  
- [ ] Ensure data privacy compliance for cross-border data transfers (e.g., GDPR)  
- [ ] Include applicable export control regulations (EAR, EU Dual-Use Regulation)  
- [ ] Apply ongoing compliance monitoring and audit rights  

**Guidelines**

- Specify Incoterms referencing the current ICC edition and named place/port  
- Screen and require ongoing screening of restricted parties and entities  
- Use neutral governing law and seat to ensure enforceability under the New York Convention  
- Exclude the CISG unless specifically intended to apply  
- Add carve-outs in limitation of liability for intellectual property, confidentiality, and compliance breaches  
- Confirm local regulatory registrations and approvals prior to contract execution  
- Maintain simple, flat lists; avoid nested bullets in deliverables  
- Mark uncertain legal citations with [VERIFY] where applicable (none included here)  

**Template Skeleton**

```text
INTERNATIONAL DISTRIBUTION AGREEMENT

1. Appointment of Distributor
2. Territory and Sales Channels
3. Orders, Pricing, and Payment
4. Delivery Terms (Incoterms)
5. Title and Risk of Loss
6. Warranty and Returns
7. Compliance with Laws and Regulations
8. Intellectual Property License
9. Confidentiality
10. Term and Termination
11. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution
12. CISG Exclusion
13. Limitation of Liability and Indemnity
14. Force Majeure
15. Assignment and Change of Control
16. Independent Contractor Relationship
17. Audit Rights and Records
18. Miscellaneous Provisions
```
